# The `CallBase` Class Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

Base class for all callable instructions (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/invokeinst">InvokeInst</a> and <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/callinst">CallInst</a>) Holds everything related to calling a function. <a href="#details">More...</a>

## Description {#details}

Base class for all callable instructions (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/invokeinst">InvokeInst</a> and <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/callinst">CallInst</a>) Holds everything related to calling a function.

All call-like instructions are required to use a common operand layout:
<ul>
<li>Zero or more arguments to the call,</li>
<li>Zero or more operand bundles with zero or more operand inputs each bundle,</li>
<li>Zero or more subclass controlled operands</li>
<li>The called function.</li>
</ul>


This allows this base class to easily access the called function and the start of the arguments without knowing how many other operands a particular subclass requires. Note that accessing the end of the argument list isn&#39;t as cheap as most other operations on the base class.

Definition at line 1112 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/ir/instrtypes-h">InstrTypes.h</a>.

<SectionDefinition>

## Operand Bundle API


This group of methods provides the API to access and manipulate operand bundles on this call.

### bundle&#95;op&#95;info&#95;begin {#a09fff26473ca9a3d9d1ff51633e048c1}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>bundle&#95;op&#95;iterator llvm::CallBase::bundle&#95;op&#95;info&#95;begin ()</>}
  labels = {["inline"]}>
Return the start of the list of <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/callbase/bundleopinfo">BundleOpInfo</a> instances associated with this OperandBundleUser.

OperandBundleUser uses the descriptor area co-allocated with the host <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/user">User</a> to store some meta information about which operands are &quot;normal&quot; operands, and which ones belong to some operand bundle.

The layout of an operand bundle user is <CodeBlock>     +-----------uint32&#95;t End-------------------------------------+
     |                                                            |
     |  +--------uint32&#95;t Begin--------------------+              |
     |  |                                          |              |
     ^  ^                                          v              v
</CodeBlock> |---|---|-|-|-|-|-|------|-|------|-|-- | BOI0 | BOI1 | .. | DU | U0 | U1 | .. | BOI0&#95;U0 | .. | BOI1&#95;U0 | .. | Un |---|---|-|-|-|-|-|------|-|------|-|-- v v ^ ^ | | | | | +-----uint32&#95;t Begin---------+ | | | +--------uint32&#95;t End--------------------------+

BOI0, BOI1 ... are descriptions of operand bundles in this <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/user">User</a>&#39;s use list. These descriptions are installed and managed by this class, and they&#39;re all instances of OperandBundleUser&lt;T&gt;::BundleOpInfo.

DU is an additional descriptor installed by <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/user">User</a>&#39;s &#39;operator new&#39; to keep track of the &#39;BOI0 ... BOIN&#39; co-allocation. OperandBundleUser does not access or modify DU in any way, it&#39;s an implementation detail private to <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/user">User</a>.

The regular <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/use">Use</a>&amp; vector for the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/user">User</a> starts at U0. The operand bundle uses are part of the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/use">Use</a>&amp; vector, just like normal uses. In the diagram above, the operand bundle uses start at BOI0&#95;U0. Each instance of <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/callbase/bundleopinfo">BundleOpInfo</a> has information about a contiguous set of uses constituting an operand bundle, and the total set of operand bundle uses themselves form a contiguous set of uses (i.e. there are no gaps between uses corresponding to individual operand bundles).

This class does not know the location of the set of operand bundle uses within the use list  that is decided by the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/user">User</a> using this class via the BeginIdx argument in populateBundleOperandInfos.

Currently operand bundle users with hung-off operands are not supported.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/ir/instrtypes-h/#l02214">2214</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/ir/instrtypes-h">InstrTypes.h</a>.
</MemberDefinition>
